The paper presents a deep generative model with an attention mechanism and external memory to capture local detail information. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it deals with generative models and attention mechanisms. Additionally, the paper also mentions the use of variational Bayesian methods, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve image generation, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of memory units is also a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also mentions missing value imputation, which is a task in natural language processing (cs.CL).
